		<span class="content_headline"><h4 align='center'>Privacy Policy</h4></span><br><br><br>

		<p>Cedars of Lebanon appreciate that privacy is very important. Cedars of Lebanon has adopted this Privacy Policy as we recognise the right of people to keep their personal information private. This Privacy Policy covers Cedars of Lebanon’s treatment of personally identifiable information that we collect or hold.
<ul class="unordered">
<li>I. Registration as a member of Cedars of Lebanon</li>
Its members are the Born again Alumni of the Christian of Mbarara University of Science and technology and their Born Again spouses. The associate membership of this organisation is open to Born-Again children of full members aged 18 years and above and any other Born-Again Christian interested in the vision of the organisation. The Associate members are required to express their interest in writing and be seconded by two (2) Cedars. All persons that fit the above description may register as members of Cedars of Lebanon and must also read, understand and agree to the Cedars of Lebanon constitution (2007)
</ul>
<li>II. The information we collect</li>
Cedars of Lebanon will collect personal information about you, such as your name, address, and contact details so we can contact you. We may also collect this and other types of personal information during the course of dealing with you, for example when you wish to get information from us or complete other forms. Where practical, the purpose for which we collect personal information will be made clear at the time of collection.
If you do not provide us with certain information or register as a member we may be unable to provide you with access to some of our services or the assistance you have requested.
Users can generally visit the Cedars of Lebanon website without revealing who they are or other personal information unless they log on or register with us. We will not collect any personal information about visitors to the website except when they knowingly provide it.

<li>III. How we use your information</li>
Cedars of Lebanon will use the personal information we collect for the purpose disclosed at the time of collection, or otherwise as set out in this Privacy Policy. We will not use your personal information for any other purpose without first seeking your consent, unless authorised or required by law. Generally we will only use and disclose your personal information as follows:
    <ol>To establish and maintain your involvement with Cedars of Lebanon, including providing you with newsletters;</ol>
    <ol>To provide the products or services you have requested from Cedars of Lebanon;</ol>
    <ol>To answer your inquiry;</ol>
    <ol>To register you for events, conferences, missions or retreats;</ol>
    <ol>To assist us to make the Cedars of Lebanon services and activities more valuable to our members and community;</ol>
    <ol>For direct promotion of activities or services and to keep you informed of new developments we believe may be of interest to you. If we contact you in this way without obtaining your prior consent, we will provide you with the opportunity to decline any further promotional communications;</ol>
    <ol>To third parties where we have retained those third parties to assist us to operate Cedars of Lebanon and provide services you have requested, such as religious education instructors, catering and event coordinators, promotions companies, transport providers, health care providers, website hosts and IT consultants, and our professional advisers such as consultants, lawyers and accountants. In some circumstances we may need to disclose sensitive information about you to third parties as part of the services you have requested.</ol>

<li>IV. Access to your information</li>
Once you have registered as a member of Cedars of Lebanon, you will have access and rights to update the personal information that we hold about you which is inaccurate, incomplete, out of date or as you may deem appropriate and necessary .

V. Security</li>
Cedars of Lebanon will take reasonable steps to keep secure any personal information which we hold and to keep this information accurate and up to date. Personal information is stored in a secure server or secure files.
The Internet is not a secure method of transmitting information. Accordingly, Cedars of Lebanon cannot accept responsibility for the security of information you send to or receive from us over the Internet or for any unauthorised access or use of that information.

<li>VI. Changes to this Privacy Policy</li>
Cedars of Lebanon may amend this Privacy Policy from time to time by having the amended version available on our website at www.iamacedar.org. We suggest that you visit our website regularly to keep up to date with any changes.

<li>VII. Contacting us</li>
If you would like any further information, or have any queries, problems or complaints relating to Cedars of Lebanon’s Privacy Policy or our information handling practices in general, please contact us by filling out the form on the contacts page, calling or writing to a Cedars of Lebanon office address near you on the contacts page.
